Date: Mon 21 Apr 2014
Source: GIDEON (Global Infectious Disease & Epidemiology Network) [edited]
http://cdn.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Pmultocida-UK.bmp


Re: ProMED-mail Meningitis, bacterial - UK: (England) domestic cat-to-human infant transm 20140420.2417385
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Few countries publish reports of _Pasteurella multocida_ infection on a national level. The incidence of human pasteurellosis in the United Kingdom increased from 172 cases in 1972, to 426 in 2006 and 466 in 2007. 5 fatal cases were reported during 1993 to 2006. Reporting trends for _P. multicida_ infection in England and Wales are depicted in the graph at http://cdn.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Pmultocida-UK.bmp.

Reference
---------
1. Berger SA: Infectious Diseases of the United Kingdom, 2014. 1154 pages, 959 graphs, 4208 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-the-united-kingdom/

